('56', '1', '2018-06-06 19:02:22', '2018-06-06 19:02:22', '<h3>SANDRA RIEGER &amp; Co. CREATES DESIGN, STORIES, AND COMMUNITIES THROUGH A HOLISTIC, COLLABORATIVE APPROACH.</h3>\r\nWe are a multidisciplinary development, design, marketing, and lifestyle firm that is passionate about purposeful living and is focused on the human experience. Guided by these principles, the firm produces its own projects, as well as collaborates with individuals, small and large businesses to create healthy, positive, and memorable experiences for the end users.\r\n\r\n<strong>Focus areas include: </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Home</li>\r\n 	<li>Restaurant</li>\r\n 	<li>Hospitality</li>\r\n 	<li>Retail</li>\r\n 	<li>Office</li>\r\n 	<li>Event</li>\r\n 	<li>Community</li>\r\n 	<li>Non-profit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<img style=\"margin:20px 0 0; class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-44\" src=\"http://sandrariegerandco.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/unnamed-225x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" />\r\n<h5 style=\"margin:0;\"><strong>Sandra Rieger, Founder &amp; Principal</strong></h5>\r\n<span>\r\n\r\nPrior to forming SR &amp; Co., Sandra Rieger worked in trend-focused marketing for some of the most recognized global retail brands, including Target Corporation in Minneapolis and Amazon.com in Seattle. As a Senior Marketing Manager, she led retail category strategy and analysis, produced world-class creative for multimillion-dollar portfolios, as well as managed cross-functional teams throughout the production process. Sandra currently holds a Minnesota Real Estate License with global brokerage, ENGEL &amp; VÖLKERS and has localized market expertise that further informs real estate development strategy, concept, and programming.\r\n\r\nSandra is a proud Minneapolis resident and passionate about community involvement and development. She has served on the West Calhoun Neighborhood Council as a board member and is currently a member advisor on the Kingfield Neighborhood Association\'